    "The predictive model generates weighted networks that, opposite to their simpler unweighted siblings, follow lognormal rather than scale-free distributions (Fig. 6; see also Supplementary Materials).",
    "This effect has been found in numerous studies on mice and macaques 57, 58, suggesting that rapid decay and high variance in connection strength arise from distance-dependent wiring costs 59.",
    "The main limitation of this study is the small sample size and the lack of an external validation dataset.",
    "Heterogeneity could also impact the results.",
    "Despite not showing inter-group differences in the time interval between scans, individual trajectories should also be considered, and thus investigated in more detail."
